--------------------------------------------
Usage: huxley mixin [command] [name]
--------------------------------------------
Follow any command with "help" for more information.

Running `init` is a prerequisiste before you can add mixins.

This sub-command allows you to at services to your application.  Each named mixin
adds a subdirectory to your application's "launch/" directory.  This contains a
template ready for your configuration and will ultimately be launched into its own
Linux container.

Commands:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  create [add]

Available Mixins:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  node.js
  elasticsearch
  kibana
  redis
